<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-06-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-06-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="1740" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1740">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 718.1915/238.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Chargé <persName type="from">Endicott</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Extract.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">San José</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-06-24">
                                    <hi rend="italic">June 24, 1915</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Costa Rican Minister for Foreign Affairs has verbally requested me to
                            inform you that an extraordinary mission from Panama headed by Santiago
                            de la Guardia accredited as Envoy Extraordinary and Minister
                            Plenipotentiary has arrived at San José with the object of reaching an
                            agreement to modify the boundary question decided by the Chief Justice;
                            that the Costa Rican Government refuses to treat of this matter with
                            Guardia as it considers that it should be settled by the judgment; and
                            that the only thing that the Costa Rican Government desires is to
                            proceed as soon as possible to matter of delimitation, for which it
                            counts on the good offices of the United States.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Endicott.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>